## 🚀 Setup

### 1. Clone Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/CyberGuard-Pro.git
cd CyberGuard-Pro
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Configure Environment
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your API keys
```

### 4. Run Locally (Polling Mode)
```bash
python bot.py
```

---

## 🔑 Environment Variables

### Required
| Variable | Description | Get It |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| `BOT_TOKEN` | Telegram Bot Token | [@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather) |
| `VT_KEY` | VirusTotal API Key | [virustotal.com](https://www.virustotal.com/gui/my-apikey) |
| `OPENAI_KEY` | OpenAI/OpenRouter API Key | [openrouter.ai](https://openrouter.ai/keys) |

### Optional (Webhook Mode)
| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `WORKER_URL` | Your Cloudflare Worker URL (e.g., `https://worker.domain.com`) |
| `WORKER_SECRET` | Secret token for webhook verification |

### Optional (API Rotation — Quota Spread)
| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GOOGLE_KEY1` | Google Safe Browsing API Key #1 |
| `GOOGLE_KEY2` | Google Safe Browsing API Key #2 |
| `URLSCAN_KEY1` | URLScan.io API Key #1 |
| `URLSCAN_KEY2` | URLScan.io API Key #2 |

### Optional (AI Customization)
| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `OPENAI_BASE` | `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1` | Custom API endpoint |
| `OPENAI_MODEL` | `openai/gpt-oss-120b:free` | Model to use |

### Optional (Server)
| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `PORT` | `8080` | Flask listen port |

