## 🌐 Deployment

### Option A: Render + Cloudflare Worker (Recommended)

**Why?** Free tier, no polling overhead, instant webhook delivery.

#### Step 1: Cloudflare Worker
```javascript
// worker.js
export default {
  async fetch(request, env) {
    const url = new URL(request.url);
    
    if (url.pathname === '/telegram' && request.method === 'POST') {
      const resp = await fetch('https://YOUR_RENDER_APP.onrender.com/telegram', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'X-Worker-Secret': env.WORKER_SECRET,
        },
        body: request.body,
      });
      return new Response(resp.body, { status: resp.status });
    }
    
    if (url.pathname === '/') {
      return new Response('🛡️ CyberGuard Worker — Active', { status: 200 });
    }
    
    return new Response('Not Found', { status: 404 });
  },
};
```

#### Step 2: Render Web Service
```bash
# In Render dashboard, set environment variables:
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token
VT_KEY=your_vt_key
OPENAI_KEY=your_openai_key
WORKER_URL=https://your-worker.your-subdomain.workers.dev
WORKER_SECRET=a_random_secret_string
PORT=8080

# Build Command:
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start Command:
python bot.py
```

#### Step 3: Set Webhook
Bot automatically sets webhook on startup if `WORKER_URL` is configured.

---

### Option B: Render Only (Polling Mode)

```bash
# Set these env vars (NO WORKER_URL):
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token
VT_KEY=your_vt_key
OPENAI_KEY=your_openai_key
PORT=8080
```

> ⚠️ Polling mode uses more RAM and has higher latency. Webhook mode is recommended.

